Anyone who gives this app fewer than 5 stars simply doesn't understand what it's made to do or how powerful it is. This is literally a complete mastering package for Android for pennies compared to what you'll pay for a DAW and then an Izotope mastering package or the like. If you're familiar with Caustic, you'll be right at home here (and it interfaces great with Caustic, too!). If you're interested in mastering audio or just want a great DSP effects suite, look no further. Bravo! More!!

The only thing I wish for is the ability to export/import directly from Caustic, currently you have to use the file system and do a little bit of fiddling with the file manager to organize your track strips during mastering. Raw WAV pcm is very large, a device with a lot of internal storage is recommended for audio mastering or a rooted device with busybox ln binary symlink for the export folder.

I got this to convert wave to MP3. It does. So I can take my musical creations from caustic to the world if I want. I bought Caustic for 10 bucks ages ago. It was awesome from the start. It's gotten better and better. You could master something properly. I'm a hobbyist really. I'm amazed at how much I've learnt about music. Simple to use yet gratifyingly complex. I cannot say enough how awesome Caustic is.

The Caustic Mastering software is top-notch. I mastered 2 songs and gotten exceptional mixes. Check out Softcell's website and if you follow the software's sequence laid out, you'll certainly will have an awesome mix. You probably won't need every single effect, but you will have a killer mix by sticking with the sequence of effects.

For a free app there's some really cool stuff here and it has potential to be awesome. The problem is that it's riddled with bugs, and that prevents it from being useful. For example, I attempted to export a quick alteration to a track and I watched it scan the track 2.5 times and then export a version of the track that plays my original track 2.5 times. It's a truly bizarre result, and I have no idea why it would do that.

This is a mastering wonder that fits in your pocket. As with any software, you have to know what you are doing. The fact that it gives you full control of the sound makes it very professional. Works great even on devices with low ram and older processors. Keep up the great work! Producer Gino Love.
